Reviews.Title: Great computer!
Reviews.Author: Ateo513
Reviews.Content: This is by far the best laptop i have ever used. I got it to replace an old DELL Latitude, and it works much better and faster too. It's fairly tough, i'm kinda clumsy and i drop the computer often. So all in all I give it 5 stars for being fast, easy to use because it came with windows 7, and tough!

Reviews.Title: Don't Buy
Reviews.Author: Doc
Reviews.Content: The price was great, and as they say you get what you pay for.  From configuration problems within the first year and now less than 2 years old and the fans have gone.  Obviously not worth fixing, so I am trying an external fan I bought for 40.00 and lets see if i get another year out of it.  Its really annoying that it keeps overheating and shutting down.  I will never buy another Toshiba laptop and definitely wouldn't recommend it even though the price is very inviting.

Reviews.Title: Great computer
Reviews.Author: puffay96 "puffy96"
Reviews.Content: I purchased my Toshiba L455-55975 two years ago. I wanted to write a review after I used the machine a while to see how it would work for me. This is the best computer for the price on the market. I work for an Early Childhood School and I am a College student. I use this computer to store children's records, lesson plans, observations and personal use. I also have taken on line classes with it. I also have used it for computer classes. During a computer training at work we had five computers to work on, a couple of Dells and HP's and my Toshiba. My Toshiba was the fastest computer. The Instructor asked if she could borrow my Toshiba for the training. I guess that speaks for itself. I highly recommend this computer.

Reviews.Title: decent laptop...for about a year
Reviews.Author: maybeTX
Reviews.Content: I bought this laptop (at Best Buy) in November 2009. Around November 2010 the mouse key dropped into the laptop. In March 2011 the battery quit working and it must be plugged in to use. I use it primarily for school, email, and research. For $350 this is expensive for only one good year of use.

Reviews.Title: Decent laptop for student
Reviews.Author: Shardule Shah
Reviews.Content: Cons:For a month or so, I couldn't click on anything until after I pressed ctrl+alt+delete; I didn't have to re-start my computer but just had to kind of jumpstart it just by pressing that combination of buttonsSound is terrible; I listen to music a lot and I always need headphones to get the proper sound (bad treble, bad bass, and bad overall 'loud' factor)Doesn't come with MS Office (apart from the 60-day trial)Pros:Any time I've had a virus problem, a quick virus clean took care of it; computer speed is still the same from the time I got itFast log-on to WindowsScreen is brightOverall, this is a decent laptop.  The battery power is okay (turn off your volume and wi-fi to get better battery power) and it runs fine.  Nothing extraordinarily great or bad about this computer.

Reviews.Title: Do not buy this laptop
Reviews.Author: Kay Heath "klassykk"
Reviews.Content: I bought this Tobisha for my husband for Christmas 2009 and 3 months later he turned it on and it was just a white screen. We tried everything we knew to do and then I called the Toshiba service center. They told me right off that the computer was still under warranty. Then he told me that it would probably cost around 425.00 to fix it. $425.00 to fix a laptop that cost me $279.00. I asked him what good was the warranty if it did not cover anything. All he gave me was the run around. So I now have a $279.00 paper weight. So my advice is stay away from Toshiba.

Reviews.Title: HAPPY DAUGHTER
Reviews.Author: P. Meredith
Reviews.Content: I purchased this for my Daughter who is in the States, she loves it and it's a great help with her college work. My disappointment is that it hasn't got a webcam and as this is also for Skype talk that's BAD.

Reviews.Title: Don't bother purchasing this
Reviews.Author: Owyhee gal
Reviews.Content: I purchased this for my husband for Christmas 2009. He went to use it for the 2nd time last night (with the first time just making a recovery disc and setting up e-mail) and it went to a white screen, with no option to do anything. We rebooted by shutting it off and on because Control, alt, delete did nothing and it came back with vertical colored lines and no matter how many times we turn it on and off, it does the same thing. Probably less than 5 hours on this machine. Pretty much defective immediately. Now that it's been more than 14 days since we purchased it (Best Buy), we have to work through the warranty service, which means we'll probably have to send it off and wait a month. UGH!!  I've had my toshiba for 1.5 years with no issue, but this one is a bummer. Only problem we've consistenly had with our Toshibas involve replacing the power cords, a lot! Get the warranty, you'll use it. Everything is so expensive when it comes to repairs.

Reviews.Title: Ugh - Would not buy it again...
Reviews.Author: C. Fry
Reviews.Content: I have a little Toshiba that is 12 years old, so thought I would love another Toshiba. Perhaps I would, but not THIS laptop. I wanted something smaller, so that part is my bad.  I wanted something lighter, and it isn't as light as I thought. It does have a DVD so that is good.The pad is hard to use, too sensitive, and you can't "tone it down" - the cursor jumps all over the page to places unknown and I'm not even using it!  I thought attaching the mouse would be "the answer" even though that sort of defeats the purpose of having a laptop.  The mouse attaches at the side, so the mouse cord is always in the way.  Irritating. And when you type, getting close to the pad makes the cursor jump out of where you are typing, so you have to go find it and kidnap it back to your app.Window's 7 isn't near as wonderful as advertised. Windows 95 was a whole lot better, so why to they keep mucking it up?All in all, I like the 12 year old one better even if it is heavier - at least it is smaller. I hate this new one.
